    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div style=\"margin-left: 10px\"><a id=\"Figure_3\"/><figure style=\"margin-left: 10px\">   <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"  > <br>  <figcaption><b>Figure 3</b>. Flux ratio KDE plots for each association \n",
       "    category. Counts are scaled by the inverse of the number of sources with nbb=1,\n",
       "    so the total represents the fraction of nbb=2 to nbb=1. The pulsars are then \n",
       "    an estimate of the contribution of false positives to be applied to the others.\n",
       "    </figcaption></figure></div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<utilities.ipynb_docgen.doc_formatter.<locals>.MimeBundleObject at 0x78341a342f50>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "Notes:\n",
       "* The range of the pulsar step sizes is  mostly limited to be less than 2.\n",
       "* If the apparent pulsar steps are all spurious, its dristribution\n",
       "above shouid be a component of all the others. This does not\n",
       "appear to be the case, especially for the unid's.\n",
       "* The asymmetry between up- and down-steps is dramatically\n",
       "different. It appears from this that the most of the bcu's are \n",
       "BL Lacs, and a large proportion of the unid's are as well."
      ],
      "text/plain": [
